flowchart TD
  Candidate[Hermes or Citadel candidate source] --> Owner{Source owner approved access?}
  Owner -- No --> NeedsOwner[Mark status needs owner decision]
  Owner -- Blocked by legal/security --> Blocked[Mark status blocked]
  Owner -- Yes --> Contract[Record access method, owner, tenant key, freshness SLA, redaction rule, and allowed signal types]
  Contract --> Tenant{Tenant boundary verified?}
  Tenant -- No --> TenantBlocked[Fail closed and create restricted-context note]
  Tenant -- Yes --> Freshness{Freshness valid?}
  Freshness -- No --> Stale[Record stale, expired, or unknown freshness without decision authority]
  Freshness -- Yes --> Redact[Create redacted source summary and safe source reference]
  Redact --> Provenance[Map summary to control-plane-context-provenance.v1 external_sources]
  Stale --> Provenance
  TenantBlocked --> Provenance
  Provenance --> Conflict{Could fact affect scope, acceptance, risk, routing, timeline, customer impact, or compliance?}
  Conflict -- Yes --> BlockingQuestion[Create PM-owned blocking question with operator resolution required]
  BlockingQuestion --> Operator{Operator resolves?}
  Operator -- No --> ContextOnly[Keep as context-only provenance]
  Operator -- Yes --> PMUpdate[PM updates authoritative artifact through normal workflow]
  Conflict -- No --> RestrictedNote[Expose role-scoped restricted-context note]
  RestrictedNote --> ContextOnly
  PMUpdate --> Authoritative[Artifact carries approved provenance reference]
  ContextOnly --> NoAuthority[No committed requirements, approvals, dispatch, closeout, or operator-intent override]
